105
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,600
Ke Yu'ang,

106
00:07:27,279 --> 00:07:29,439
you made the superior very angry.

107
00:07:32,279 --> 00:07:34,720
Xue Li said he had checked the goods,

108
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:37,040
It must be him who did it.

109
00:07:40,279 --> 00:07:42,160
You don't have much time left.

110
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:45,199
Only by finding the key can you redeem yourself.

111
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:25,959
Xue Li must have tampered with the jade disc.

112
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:29,480
Is the key on the jade disc?

113
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,240
This is the real key you want.

114
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:19,440
The key is indeed carved on the jade disc.

115
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,759
Damn it, Xue Li.

116
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,080
How did you get this?

117
00:09:54,279 --> 00:09:56,120
Is the missing key

118
00:09:57,159 --> 00:09:59,320
on Jiang Xun?

119
00:10:06,679 --> 00:10:07,799
Xue Li changed his mind

120
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,320
and clashed with me at the museum that day,

121
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:11,399
breaking the jade disc.

122
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,360
I checked with people from Mingzhen.

123
00:10:13,799 --> 00:10:14,919
They said

124
00:10:14,919 --> 00:10:16,879
Xue Li did tamper with the jade disc.

125
00:10:17,399 --> 00:10:18,320
I think

126
00:10:18,639 --> 00:10:20,120
he and Xu Mo joined forces

127
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,720
to set us up.

128
00:10:24,759 --> 00:10:26,080
So you killed him.

129
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,879
Xue Li was being followed at that time.

130
00:10:28,399 --> 00:10:29,559
He couldn't escape from Rongzhou.

131
00:10:29,679 --> 00:10:30,600
If he didn't die,

132
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:32,159
he would have exposed everyone.

133
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:34,080
Then your plan

134
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,360
would have been ruined.

135
00:10:35,759 --> 00:10:38,080
Now Xu has been arrested.

136
00:10:38,919 --> 00:10:40,320
If he knows the key,

137
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,279
he will definitely tell the Security Bureau.

138
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,120
You and I wouldn't be standing here.

139
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,080
You killed the only person

140
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,720
who knew the key in the world.

141
00:10:53,759 --> 00:10:54,600
Do you think

142
00:10:55,559 --> 00:10:56,679
if the higher-ups find out

143
00:10:56,679 --> 00:10:58,320
you did such a stupid thing,

144
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,159
will they kill you?

145
00:11:01,879 --> 00:11:05,080
You better confirm where the key is.

146
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,759
The key might be in Jiang Xun's hands.

147
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,360
I'm not sure.

148
00:11:11,919 --> 00:11:14,159
Then go confirm it.

149
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,679
Xue Li uses the jade disc as the key carrier.

150
00:11:54,679 --> 00:11:57,320
[The missing four digits need to be verified through the jade pendant.]

151
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,639
[Encrypting messages]

152
00:11:58,639 --> 00:12:01,440
is the usual method of foreign espionage and intelligence agencies.

153
00:12:01,559 --> 00:12:04,080
From the secret writing techniques of the Cold War era

154
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:06,080
to the blockchain steganography of today,

155
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:09,480
encryption technology has become more advanced and covert.

156
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:12,200
But whether it's a carefully designed code

157
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,360
or the ever-changing black technology,

158
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:16,480
there are always traces.

159
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,440
In the face of the determination

160
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,600
and wisdom in defending national security,

161
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,360
conspiracies will eventually be exposed.
